explanation: This solution uses a binary search approach to efficiently find the target number. It maintains a range [left, right] and repeatedly narrows it down by guessing the middle number. If the guess is correct, it returns the number. If the guess is higher, it updates the right boundary. If the guess is lower, it updates the left boundary. The time complexity is O(log n) because the range is halved in each iteration.

